The paper deals with the complexity of comparison of influence between players in coalitional voting games, which is a topic in game theory and social choice. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of classical power indices such as Shapley-Shubik index, Banzhaf index, Holler index, Deegan-Packel index and Chow parameters, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The paper also examines the complexity of transforming simple games into compact representations, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of desirability relations, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of computing certain values, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.LG).
